        jTextArea1.setText("When a person is underweight, \nit indicates that their body might not be receiving sufficient nutrients to support the\n development of healthy bones, skin, and hair. This can lead to various \nrelated symptoms and signs, such as osteoporosis, a condition characterized \nby brittle bones; anemia, which can cause fatigue and weakness; as well as a \ngeneral feeling of tiredness and potential hair and skin issues. Proper nutrition\n is crucial to maintain a healthy weight and support overall well-being.\n\nIf you're underweight, it's important to focus on eating foods that provide plenty of energy to help you gain weight, \nas well as protein to repair your body and build muscle, and vitamins and minerals to support overall health. \nHere are some additional tips:\n\n- Set a realistic goal for weight gain and work towards it gradually.\n- Make sure to eat regularly, aiming for at least three meals a day and not skipping breakfast.\n- Increase your calorie intake to be higher than the amount you burn in a day, while still maintaining a balanced diet.\n- Start by adding an extra 300 to 350 calories per day to your diet and adjust as needed.\n- Incorporate low-impact strengthening exercises such as yoga or Pilates into your routine.\n- Keep a food diary for a few weeks to track your eating habits and identify areas where you can make improvements.");
