        jTextArea2.setText("Being overweight or obese can significantly impact health, as carrying excess fat can\n lead to serious consequences. These include cardiovascular diseases, such as heart \ndisease and stroke, type 2 diabetes, and musculoskeletal disorders like \nosteoarthritis. Additionally, being overweight increases the risk of certain cancers, \nsuch as endometrial, breast, and colon cancer. These conditions can result in \npremature death and substantial disability, highlighting the importance of \nmaintaining a healthy weight.\n\nIf you're overweight, losing weight will give you more energy and help to reduce the risk of obesity. \nHere are some tips for losing weight, You do not have to do everything at once, \ntry one thing at a time and find what works for you :\n\n- Cut down on food that's high in sugar and fat \n- Aim to lose 1/2 - 1 kg per week\n- Avoid sugary drinks or sodas and replace it with water\n- Resize your food portions, eat less carbs and more protein \n- Do physical activities more and do exercises at least 3 times a week\n- Eat more nutritious food, you can customize with your food preferences");
